    <hard>
        <question>
            <text>General Doppler formula: f_obs = f_src (v ± vo) / (v ∓ vs). vo is ____ speed.</text>
            <option id="A">Observer</option><option id="B">Source</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Standard relative frequency equation.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>In Doppler effect, vs is source speed. If vs = v/2 move towards stationary observer, freq becomes ____.</text>
            <option id="A">2 f_src</option><option id="B">1.5 f_src</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>f' = f (v) / (v - v/2) = f * 2.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>A tuning fork A produces 4 beats/s with B of freq 256 Hz. If A is filed, beat freq increases. Freq of A was ____.</text>
            <option id="A">260 Hz</option><option id="B">252 Hz</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Filing increases freq. If it was 260, filing move it further from 256.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Wavefront is a surface on which all points have same ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Phase</option><option id="B">Amplitude</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Spatial wave surface property.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Group velocity v_g = d____ / d____.</text>
            <option id="A">w / k</option><option id="B">k / w</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Speed of wave packet in dispersive medium.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Phase velocity v_p and Group velocity v_g in deep water waves: v_g = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">v_p / 2</option><option id="B">v_p</option><option id="C">none</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Derived from dispersion relation w ∝ sqrt(k).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Intensity of sound at distance r from point source varies as ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1 / r^2</option><option id="B">1 / r</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Inverse square law (Power / 4πr^2).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Pressure amplitude of sound in air for hearing threshold (0 dB) is approx ____ Pa.</text>
            <option id="A">2 x 10^-5</option><option id="B">10^5</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Extremely sensitive detection limit.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Two open organ pipes L1 and L2 produce beats. Beat freq f = ____.</text>
